    </title>

    <description>
Mary Jo volunteers with Habitat for Humanity to recover and possibly
repair damaged homes in Montacito, California. She is sensitive to the
residents and what they have lost, the most important things not being
the furniture and other "hard" items but the memories.  She recalls
finding an intact photo album and recounting as the owner sat down in
tears, leafing through the pages of photos. to Mary Jo it is about
community, where everyone knows somebody that knows somebody...
